title: British gymnasts hit new high to make sure of maximum numbers at Rio Olympics - Basingstoke Gazette
text:
Great Britain's exceptional display at the World Gymnastics Championships in Glasgow means they will send a full women's team to next year's Olympics. Requiring a top-eight finish after the two-day qualification competition, the 227.162-point score not only ensures their place in Tuesday's team final but, most importantly, the Games in Rio de Janeiro.
 Basingstoke Gazette.
